 AGAIN the wood  and long withdrawing vale  In many a tint of tender green are drest  Where the young leaves unfolding  scarce conceal Beneath their early shade  the half form nest Of finch or woodlark  and the primrose pale  And lavish cowslip  wildly scatter round  Give their sweet spirits to the sighing gale  Ah  season of delight    could aught be found To footh awhile the tortured bosom pain  Of Sorrow rankling shaft to cure the wound  And bring life first delusions once again   Twere surely met in thee    thy prospect fair  Thy sounds of harmony  thy balmy air  Have power to cure all sadne   but despair 
